f billions of dollars in a new generation of satellites it calls theProliferated Warfighter Space Architecture.\", \"from\": 213, \"to\": 544, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 213, \"end\": 232, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Supreme_Commander_for_the_Allied_Powers\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"US military leaders\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Supreme_Commander_for_the_Allied_Powers\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Supreme_Commander_for_the_Allied_Powers\"}, {\"begin\": 248, \"end\": 253, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999998976641161, \"rank\": 9.000628764183984e-08, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 402, \"end\": 404, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Armed_Forces\", \"score\": 0.6326161885174917, \"rank\": 0.5773611696582897, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q176799\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Armed_Forces\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Armed_Forces\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"its military space\", \"from\": 266, \"to\": 284}, {\"ngram\": \"counterspace capabilities\", \"from\": 289, \"to\": 314}, {\"ngram\": \"breathtaking pace,\\\"Russiamay\", \"from\": 318, \"to\": 346}, {\"ngram\": \"a nuclear anti-satellite weapon\", \"from\": 361, \"to\": 392}, {\"ngram\": \"tens of billions\", \"from\": 427, \"to\": 443}, {\"ngram\": \"dollars\", \"from\": 447, \"to\": 454}, {\"ngram\": \"a new generation\", \"from\": 458, \"to\": 474}, {\"ngram\": \"satellites\", \"from\": 478, \"to\": 488}, {\"ngram\": \"theProliferated Warfighter Space Architecture\", \"from\": 498, \"to\": 543}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At the same time, a single US company, SpaceX, now controls nearly two-thirds of all operational satellites in space, and NASA is racing to return astronauts to the Moon before a joint Chinese-Russian effort gets there first.\", \"from\": 545, \"to\": 770, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 572, \"end\": 574, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Armed_Forces\", \"score\": 0.6326161885174917, \"rank\": 0.5773611696582897, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q176799\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Armed_Forces\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Armed_Forces\"}, {\"begin\": 584, \"end\": 590, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/SpaceX\", \"score\": 0.999999999128022, \"rank\": 8.719021551152265e-10, \"text\": \"SpaceX\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/SpaceX\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/SpaceX\"}, {\"begin\": 667, \"end\": 671, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NASA\", \"score\": 0.9999999981077963, \"rank\": 1.2048733566993672e-09, \"text\": \"NASA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NASA\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NASA\"}, {\"begin\": 710, \"end\": 714, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moon\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9242708289229928e-17, \"text\": \"Moon\", \"types\": [\"Q634\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moon\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Moon\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the same time\", \"from\": 548, \"to\": 561}, {\"ngram\": \"nearly two-thirds\", \"from\": 605, \"to\": 622}, {\"ngram\": \"all operational satellites\", \"from\": 626, \"to\": 652}, {\"ngram\": \"space\", \"from\": 656, \"to\": 661}, {\"ngram\": \"astronauts\", \"from\": 692, \"to\": 702}, {\"ngram\": \"a joint Chinese-Russian effort\", \"from\": 722, \"to\": 752}]}, {\"sentence\": \"These developments naturally draw comparisons to the space race that occurred during the Cold War, leading some analysts to conclude that we are now in aSpace Race 2.0.\", \"from\": 772, \